tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE consumer (
    consumer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    consumer_name VARCHAR(50),
    consumer_age INT,
    consumer_gender VARCHAR(10),
    consumer_location VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE consumer_behavior (
    behavior_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    consumer_id INT,
    influencer_id INT,
    behavior_type VARCHAR(50),
    behavior_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (consumer_id) REFERENCES consumer(consumer_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (influencer_id) REFERENCES influencer(influencer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE posts (
    post_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    influencer_id INT REFERENCES influencers(influencer_id),
    post_content TEXT,
    likes_count INT,
    comments_count INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE comments (
    comment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    post_id INT REFERENCES posts(post_id),
    commenter_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    comment_text TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE Posts (
  post_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  influencer_id INT,
  post_content TEXT,
  likes_count INT,
  comments_count INT
);

CREATE TABLE Interactions (
  interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  influencer_id INT,
  follower_id INT,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
  interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP
);
